data.description: Tax appraised at $241,920 FINALLY, an AFFORDABLE, SITE-BUILT LAKEHOUSE. 2 bedrooms and 2 baths with a large family room overlooking the expansive backyard with huge trees and covered deck. Recently vacated, fresh and clean, large rooms, stylish for the age. Excellent condition. Circle drive for plenty of parking, quiet cul-de-sac street in desireable Lakewood Forest III. There is a boathouse that spans the waterfront channel which is a 2-owner shared facility. Nearby POA boat launch for larger boats. LOVELY, WELL-BUILT HOME on CHANNEL OF LAKE LBJ in Kingsland's Lakewood Forest III. Located on a cul-de-sac street, you'll appreciate the large oak trees in front and back and the paved circle drive to park your family and friends. There is a boathouse but it may not be sufficient for all boats. The POA boat ramp is nearby for larger boats. Although only 2 specific bedrooms, the enclosed porch is plenty roomy for bunks, daybeds, or other accomodations for extra people. In great condition, vacant and easy to show, please call!
